pageContext.claim: “If you look at the number -- I mean, this was -- I think it was worse than Katrina. It was in many ways worse than anything people have ever seen.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump claiming Hurricane Marina is worse than Hurricane Katrina is a shift from when Trump visited the island, at which point he declared that, because of the low death toll in Puerto Rico, it paled in comparison with the “real catastrophe” in New Orleans in 2005.
